!# Hello! Here is an attempt at the Ubuntu Ambiance theme for Openbox.
!#
!# As of now (19/11/11) you might need to use openbox git in order to 
!# have the different coloured buttons.
!#
!#
!# -The split gradient has changed a little from Maverick to Oneiric, this is 
!# slightly tougher in openbox as the split point is a bit harsher than in the 
!# metacity/unity theme.
!#
!# -Title bar is basically fatter like in unity.
!#
!# -Title bar buttons have been tweaked a little based on pixmaps in the unity 
!# folder of the theme from ubuntu, the shade buttons probably need to be better.
!#
!# -Fixed up some of the nags from the original theme, such as the osd 
!# looking a bit wonky and having some blue highlights
!#
!# -Take advantage of Openboxâ€™s new (since 3.5) OSD theme options 
!# such as themeing the buttons and popup osd more independently.
!#
!#

!# height might need adjusting per font, Ambiance titles are quite fat.
padding.height: 4

!# maybe we need a bit of this? It'll look fine if you do, probably.
window.handle.width:0

!# General
padding.width: 4
border.Width: 1
window.client.padding.width: 0
window.client.padding.height: 0
menu.overlap: 2
window.frameColor: #353531
window.*.client.color: #353531
*.text.justify: left

!# Set *all* fonts here

menu.items.font:shadow=y:shadowtint=13:shadowoffset=1
